Harcourt Brace Jovanovich Incmanagers who use a special cash dividend to buy additionalstock are demonstrating confidence in the company, chairmanWilliam Jovanovich said.    In a written statement Jovanovich said the company'srecapitalization, which will pay a dividend of 40 dlrs pershare in cash and preferred stock worth 10 dlrs per share, isnot a leveraged buyout.    He said management of Harcourt is not receiving shares inthe recapitalization other than through a legal employee stockownership program.  Reuter&#3;